A deadly crash involving multiple vehicles has closed down traffic on the N3 South near the Barry Marais offramp. William Ntladi, Ekurhuleni Emergency Services Spokesperson said that preliminary reports confirm that the accident involved a combination of vehicles including, a truck, a taxi and two light vehicles. Ntladi said four of the vehicles in the crash burnt completely including the taxi. Tladi said that they have 7 confirmed dead at the moment. "One body in the taxi was burnt beyond recognition. We also have a another body in a bakkie that is still trapped in the wreckage. Ntladi said that five of the bodies were scattered around the crash site. "An unconfirmed number of people have also been taken to hospitals nearby," Ntladi said. 